CONTEXT KleeneEmptyRelation IN ENGLISH

PURPOSE CONTEXT KleeneEmptyRelation MARKDOWN
{+ The empty relation is the classic counterexample to the unsound law
   r* = r;r* (which would make r* empty). The sound semantics gives
   r* = I even when r has no pairs at all. Node gets its atoms from a helper
   relation and an explicit concept population (including an isolated atom).
+}

RELATION r[Node*Node]      -- deliberately unpopulated

RELATION anchor[Node*Node] -- provides atoms a and b
POPULATION anchor CONTAINS [ ("a","b") ]

POPULATION Node CONTAINS [ "c" ] -- an isolated atom; must appear in r* too

RULE starIsId  : r* = I[Node]
RULE plusEmpty : r+ |- -V[Node*Node]
RULE redEmpty  : r% |- -V[Node*Node]

INTERFACE Empty : "_SESSION"[SESSION] ; V[SESSION*Node]
   CRud BOX<TABLE sortable>
   [ "node"  : I[Node]  cRud
   , "rStar" : r*       cRud
   , "rPlus" : r+       cRud
   , "rRed"  : r%       cRud
   ]

ENDCONTEXT
